<body>

    <div id="presentation-container">
        <div class="slide" id="slide-1">
            <h1 class="question-number">Question 1</h1>
            <p class="problem-text">An urn contains **5 red** and **5 black** balls. A ball is drawn at random, its colour is noted and is returned to the urn. Moreover, **2 additional balls** of the colour drawn are put in the urn and then a ball is drawn at random.</p>
            <h2 class="main-query">What is the probability that the second ball is red?</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="slide" id="slide-2">
            <h1 class="question-number">Question 2</h1>
            <p class="problem-text">A bag contains **4 red** and **4 black** balls, another bag contains **2 red** and **6 black** balls. One of the two bags is selected at random and a ball is drawn from the bag which is found to be **red**.</p>
            <h2 class="main-query">Find the probability that the ball is drawn from the first bag.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="slide" id="slide-3">
            <h1 class="question-number">Question 3 (Bayes' Theorem)</h1>
            <ul class="data-points">
                <li>**Hostel:** P(H) = 0.60, P(A|H) = 0.30</li>
                <li>**Day Scholars:** P(D) = 0.40, P(A|D) = 0.20</li>
            </ul>
            <h2 class="main-query">Given a student has an A grade (A), what is the probability the student is a hostlier (H)? Find P(H|A).</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="slide" id="slide-4">
            <h1 class="question-number">Question 4 (Bayes' Theorem)</h1>
            <ul class="data-points">
                <li>**P(Knows):** $P(K) = \frac{3}{4}$</li>
                <li>**P(Guesses):** $P(G) = \frac{1}{4}$</li>
                <li>**P(Correct|Guesses):** $P(C|G) = \frac{1}{4}$</li>
                <li>**P(Correct|Knows):** $P(C|K) = 1$ (Implied)</li>
            </ul>
            <h2 class="main-query">What is the probability that the student knows the answer given that he answered it correctly (C)? Find P(K|C).</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="slide" id="slide-14">
            <h1 class="question-number">Question 14 (Condition)</h1>
            <p class="problem-text">If A and B are two events such that $\mathbf{A \subset B}$ and $P(B) \neq 0$, then which of the following is correct?</p>
            <div class="mcq-options">
                <p>(A) $P(B) P(A | B) / P(A) = 1$</p>
                <p>(B) $P(A|B) < P(A)$</p>
                <p>**(C) $P(A|B) \geq P(A)$**</p>
                <p>(D) None of these</p>
            </div>
            <p class="note">**Hint:** If $A \subset B$, then $A \cap B = A$. Use $P(A|B) = P(A \cap B) / P(B)$</p>
        </div>

        <div class="slide" id="slide-end">
            <h1 class="question-number">End of Presentation</h1>
            <h2 class="main-query">Thank you! Click to restart.</h2>
        </div>
    </div>

